arität und Macht stehen dabei im Mittelpunkt. Die Tarifrunde begreifen sie dabei als praktischen Auftakt für eine Zukunftsdebatte über die Rolle von Gewerkschaften, Mitbestimmung und Beteiligung in einer Gesellschaft im Umbruch.  aIG Metall has put the issue of working hours on the agenda: for more self-determination for employees. In this book, actors describe the progression and outcome of the 2018 negotiations in the metallurgical and electronics industries and shed light on key elements of trade union action, such as justice, autonomy, solidarity and power. They see the negotiations as a practical prelude to a debate on the future of trade unions, co-determination, and participation in a changing society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aCollective bargainingzGermanyxHistoryy21st century. 0aHours of laborzGermanyxHistoryy21st century. 0aIndustrial relationszGermanyxHistoryy21st century. 0aLabor unionszGermanyxHistoryy21st century. 0aMetal-workersxLabor unionszGermanyxHistoryy21st century. 0aSociology (General). 0aStrikes and lockoutszGermanyxHistoryy21st century. 0aWagesxMetal-workerszGermanyxHistoryy21st century. 4aArbeit. 4aArbeits- und Industriesoziologie. 4aArbeitspolitik. 4aArbeitszeit. 4aGesellschaft. 4aIndustrielle Beziehungen. 4aSoziale Ungleichheit. 4aSozialpolitik. 4aSozialstaat. 4aSoziologie. 4aStreik. 4aTarifpolitik. 4aVereinbarkeit. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aCollective Bargaining.  aIndustrial Relations.  aSocial Inequality.  aSocial Policy.  aSociety.  aSociology of Work and Industry.  aSociology.  aStrikes.  aWelf